From: Sam <samuelngs@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 07:16:34 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 14/15] window: preserve screen position in headless SetBounds

RenderWidgetHostViewMac::SetBounds() in headless mode calls
OnWindowFrameInScreenChanged(rect) where rect is the content
bounds with origin (0,0). This overwrites window_frame_in_screen_dip_
and causes window.screenX/screenY to always report 0.

Preserve the existing window frame origin when updating bounds
so that the screen position set by SetWindowFrameInScreen persists
across view resizes.

diff --git a/content/browser/renderer_host/render_widget_host_view_mac.mm b/content/browser/renderer_host/render_widget_host_view_mac.mm
index 63041c4311..3a6a895cd8 100644
--- a/content/browser/renderer_host/render_widget_host_view_mac.mm
+++ b/content/browser/renderer_host/render_widget_host_view_mac.mm
@@ -619,7 +619,8 @@ void RenderWidgetHostViewMac::SetBounds(const gfx::Rect& rect) {
   // propagation. This occurs while running headless and causes problems with
   // RenderDocument. See more details here: http://crbug.com/444226873.
   if (IsHeadless()) {
-    OnWindowFrameInScreenChanged(rect);
+    gfx::Rect frame(window_frame_in_screen_dip_.origin(), rect.size());
+    OnWindowFrameInScreenChanged(frame);
   }
 }
 
